message.content:
Upgrade the visual foundation of the IT asset management app at `/Users/admin/it-asset/`. Read every file before editing.

## 1. `app/globals.css` — Global visual upgrade

Make these changes:

a) Increase `--radius` from `0.625rem` to `0.75rem` in the `:root` block (line 89)

b) Change `--background` in `:root` from `oklch(1 0 0)` (pure white) to `oklch(0.985 0 0)` (very subtle warm gray). This creates visual separation between the page background and card surfaces.

c) Change `--card` in `:root` from `oklch(1 0 0)` to `oklch(1 0 0)` — keep card pure white so it pops against the slightly gray background.

d) Add custom scrollbar styles after the `@layer base` block:
```css
/* Custom scrollbar */
::-webkit-scrollbar {
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
}
::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
  background: transparent;
}
::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
  background: oklch(0.7 0 0 / 0.3);
  border-radius: 3px;
}
::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
  background: oklch(0.7 0 0 / 0.5);
}
```

e) Add selection color at the end:
```css
::selection {
  background: oklch(0.55 0.18 250 / 0.2);
}
```

f) Add global heading tracking in the `@layer base` block:
```css
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
}
```

g) For `.dark` block, change `--background` to `oklch(0.13 0 0)` (slightly darker), keep `--card` at `oklch(0.205 0 0)`.

## 2. `components/ui/card.tsx` — Shadow-based cards

Read the file first. The Card component currently uses `border bg-card text-card-foreground`. Change to use shadow instead of hard border:

- Card root: add `shadow-sm` class, keep `border` but make it subtle
- The Card should feel elevated from the background
- Add `transition-shadow` for smooth hover effects on interactive cards
- Read the file and adjust the root Card className

## 3. `components/layout/header.tsx` — Glass-morphism

Read the file first. Change the header to use glass-morphism effect:

- Add `backdrop-blur-md` to the header
- Change bg to `bg-background/80` (semi-transparent)
- Keep the border-b
- The header is at line ~70 where the className is defined. Find the header element and update its className.

## Verification
Run `npx tsc --noEmit` from the project directory after all edits. Fix any errors.

